    "Of course, the creative process already occurred in the programmer's work, when he devised and implemented the algorithm.",
    "Fig. 3 Part of the game tree for tic-tac-toe, i.e., the tree that follows all possible moves of the game",
    "The declarative logic paradigm is based on logical reasoning foot_1.",
    "The programmer specifies a set of true facts and rules (logical implications) as the knowledge base foot_2 of the program.",
    "The user of a logic program can ask for a goal (a conclusion they are trying to prove true), and an inference engine (a unique algorithm, common to all logic programs, that implements an inference procedure, based on modus ponens foot_3) tries to apply facts and rules to derive the goal."
